summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeThis hydrating, longwear foundation delivers a natural, skin-like glow all day long. Its lightweight, medium coverage formula keeps you looking fresh and smooth, while brightening and improving your skin tone instantly and over time. Itâ€™s waterproof and resistant to sweat, humidity + transfer.
details: DetailsBenefitsProvides all-day hydrationNatural, skin-like glow finishLightweight, medium coverageBrightens and improves skin instantly + over timeLongwear, waterproof + resists creasing, fading, sweat, humidity + transferColor-true pigments designed to resist oxidation all dayKey IngredientsCyperus Papyrus Leaf Cell Extract to help provide all-day hydrationKakadu Plum Extract, rich in antioxidants, to help brighten + improve skin tone overtimeItem 2624152How To UsePrep:Be sure to moisturize skin before applying foundation.Always shake before use for smooth application.For medium coverage: Apply 1 pump of Soft'Lit Foundation to the back of your hand. reviews.headline: Best Foundation I've Used
reviews.comments: I love the way this foundation makes my skin feel.  I'm 64 yo with dark spots on my face and pretty big pores.  I tried a full coverage foundation, but it felt sticky and clogged my pores causing breakouts.  So, went to Ulta to check on a medium coverage foundation.  I loved the different tints that Fenty Beauty had, so I decided to buy it.  This foundation went on smoothly (I used a brush) and gave good coverage of my dark spots.  It feels soft and is not cakey or sticky.  I bought shade 150, which looks good, but I probably could've went to 175 or 185, especially for evening and for summer months when my face gets more color to it.  I put on primer or a light moisturizer before applying with a brush, which helps to minimize my pores.  I do have a setting powder that helps to further minimize pores.  This foundation does not feel greasy or is it overly moist-appearing.

reviews.headline: Where's the glow?
reviews.comments: I bought this foundation with THE HIGHEST expectations after hearing only positive reviews, it let me down entirely. I live in AZ & have issues with sweating through my base, so the longevity of this paired with a 'natural finish' was intriguing. I'm not sure what is wrong but, no matter what prep I do, this goes on like chalk. My face feels completely dried out & theres no trace of luminosity, just very flat/patchy makeup that in no way looks like my own skin. The positives are that it does last all day & the color match is very close, the negatives are literally everything else.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I've tried many different foundations, but when I used Fenty Beauty by Rihanna Soft'Lit Naturally Luminous Hydrating Longwear Foundation, I was truly impressedâ€¦.
**Initial Impressions:**
From the very first use, I was drawn to the product's elegant and sophisticated design. The pump dispenses just the right amount of product, enough to evenly apply across the face without wasting any.
**Texture and Feel on the Skin:**
When applying this foundation, the texture is moderately liquid, making it easy to blend without feeling heavy or suffocating. My skin is combination, so I'm often concerned about foundations feeling too thick, but this product doesn't cause any issues at all. The foundation seamlessly blends into the skin, creating a smooth and natural finish.
**Coverage:**
I'm really impressed with the coverage of this foundation. It effectively conceals small blemishes and uneven skin tone. Even when I only apply a thin layer, the coverage is still solid. However, if I want to cover larger imperfections, I simply add a bit more product to the specific areas, and the difference is noticeable.
**Natural Effect and Overall Look:**
What I love most about this product is the natural effect it provides. My skin looks healthy and radiant without being too shiny or too matte. The foundation also has good moisturizing properties, so my skin doesn't dry out or flake throughout the day. Even after a few hours, when my skin naturally produces oil, the foundation still looks fresh without fading or becoming patchy. However, I did find that the tone of this product was a bit too dark for my skin tone.

**Longevity:**
Throughout the day, I noticed that this foundation adheres very well to the skin. Whether in hot and humid conditions or during periods of activity, the foundation stays put for 8-10 hours without needing much touch-up. This is a major plus for a longwear foundation like this one.

**Final Thoughts:**
Fenty Beauty by Rihanna Soft'Lit Naturally Luminous Hydrating Longwear Foundation has truly won me over with its design, quality, and effect on my skin. This is a product I will continue to use long-term, especially for occasions where I need a beautiful, long-lasting, and natural-looking foundation. I highly recommend you try it if you're looking for a foundation that offers great hydration and a radiant, natural finish.
faceoff_positive.headline: I love it

faceoff_negative.comments:
I have very dry skin but have never had an issue with texture from foundation. I do not need primer for foundation to adhere or last. I set all foundations with loose powder. My skin is not perfect but it is even enough in tone and texture that I mostly only wear eye makeup and translucent powder. Foundation is something I use for photoshoots  or special events. I have a special event at the end of the month so I'm breaking out the full face for the first time in 3 years.

I spent an hour in Ulta swatching every foundation to find a replacement for the last product I used which was discontinued a few years ago. Instead I found I had no choices due to poor color matches (and the ones suggested by the Findation tool were laughably off). The only brand that came close to my shade (for reference I used to wear Peach Perfect in Marshmallow and Colourpop concealer in 7C) was Fenty. Both foundations in 100 and the tint in shade 1. The Soft Matte foundation was slightly more yellow so I selected the Luminous foundation which had a more pink tone. 

I prepped my clean face with my usual moisturizer, Clinique Moisture Surge Intense, and applied with a damp beauty sponge. Applied that way it was sheer, streaky, and gathered notably in my pores. My T-zone had a terrible appearance of pink skin with bright beige spots and blotches. I have never had any product gather or settle in pores prior to the 12 hr point before, and certainly not AT APPLICATION. To give it a chance I removed everything and tried again, without the moisturizer base. I tried applying to my forehead with a flat top foundation brush, which gave my face the texture of sliced crumbly bread. I tried again with my fingers and a puff, essentially fingerpainting my face and then blending and pressing it into the skin with the puff. I got the best texture this way. But it still looked like curdled milk, especially in my T-zone and upper lip.

 For a luminous hydrating foundation, this was the worst I've ever worked with and looked horrendous, including the ELF foundation that gave my full-face hives for a month. It's truly a shame, because color 100 matched my face and neck perfectly. I'm returning it immediately.
faceoff_negative.headline: Separated like spoiled milk
